In this lab, I simulated a basic security assessment scenario where an attacker attempts to gain access to a remote Linux system using discovered credentials. 
The exercise demonstrated how weak password practices can lead to unauthorized system access and how attackers may attempt to escalate privileges after gaining an initial foothold.
The target machine was accessed through SSH (Secure Shell) from a remote terminal environment.


OBJECTIVE:
The goal of the exercise was to:

Attempt login access using discovered credentials
Authenticate to a remote system using SSH
Navigate the Linux filesystem
Read files and inspect system information
Identify additional users and attempt further access


